MAPUTO -Â Mozambique's opposition leader Afonso Dhlakama has died, state broadcaster TVM said on Thursday. BBC News: Mozambique's main opposition Renamo party says its long-serving leader, Afonso Dhlakama, has died of a heart attack. He was sixty-five. Mr Dhlakama led Renamo during a fifteen-year rebellion against the Mozambican government, which ended in 1992. The 65-year-old former guerrilla commander was found dead at his home in Gorongosa, it said. The circumstances of his death were not immediately clear. Reuters